      "message": "[🔴 Critical Issues] Line 38: This treats PRIORITY_UNKNOWN the same as normal priority and drops the push while the app is backgrounded. That is a risky behavior change: if FCM does not expose the original priority for any message, including a time-sensitive call/setup push, the app will skip wake lock, service startup, daemon processing, and message handling entirely. Only explicitly normal-priority pushes should be skipped; unknown should preserve the previous safe behavior. Suggested fix:\n```suggestion\n        val priority \u003d remoteMessage.originalPriority\n        val isNormal \u003d priority \u003d\u003d RemoteMessage.PRIORITY_NORMAL\n        val appInForeground \u003d isAppInForeground()\n        if (isNormal \u0026\u0026 !appInForeground) {\n            Log.d(TAG, \"Push: normal priority in background, skipping\")\n            return\n        }\n```\nThen reuse `appInForeground` below instead of calling `isAppInForeground()` again.",
